Generates responses
💾 2. Memory (Persistence Layer)
Saves conversation history
Loads conversation history
🎛️ 3. App Controller (Orchestrator)
Receives user input
Sends it to AI
Gets response
Updates memory
📡 4. Interface (Input/Output)
Prints messages
Takes user input (CLI for now)
3. System Flow (THIS is the “wiring diagram”)

This is the most important part.

User Input
   ↓
app.py (controller)
   ↓
memory.py → loads past conversation
   ↓
llm.py → generates response
   ↓
app.py → receives response
   ↓
memory.py → saves updated conversation
   ↓
Output to user

This is your “Titan architecture.”

